b'\xe2\x80\x9cYou more or less have to get out of the way and let women lead\xe2\x80\x9d.

After witnessing the pay disparity facing female basketball players earlier this year, @kyrieirving launched the \xe2\x80\x9cKai Empowerment Initiative\xe2\x80\x9d which provided financial support for WNBA players who sat out the season for health and/or advocacy reasons.\xc2\xa0

He talked to his sister @asiairving about his life-long commitment to fight for\xc2\xa0gender equality.
\xe2\xa0\x80
What\xe2\x80\x99s one cause that\xe2\x80\x99s motivating you right now? Drop a comment\xc2\xa0:backhand_index_pointing_down:'

b'Ballet + Jazz + Hip-Hop Majorettes = Compton Divas battle squad :nail_polish_dark_skin_tone:

This 15-girl strong \xe2\x80\x9cbattle squad\xe2\x80\x9d brings the heat. From krumping to balletic extensions, one thing is sure: the @divasofcompton speak the language of movement, and their passion for dance fuels cheering crowds far and wide. We can hear the stands going wild from here.

Tag your favorite dance crews below.

:camera_with_flash:@nico_therin captured before the lockdowns in 2020.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cThere is hope for many other Ingrids to be part of the dance world."
\xe2\xa0\x80
@IngridSilva founded @BlacksInBallet to uplift Black dancers in the white-centric ballet world. Growing up in Brazil, she didn\xe2\x80\x99t have role models in professional ballet that looked like her. So, she became what she never had.
\xe2\xa0\x80
Follow @BlacksInBallet to see how Ingrid\xe2\x80\x99s setting the stage for the future.
\xe2\xa0\x80
:movie_camera:: @dayday.studio @bennncareyyy'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cThere\xe2\x80\x99s something so magical and liberating about being in and near the water. Every woman deserves the right to experience that feeling.\xe2\x80\x9d
\xe2\xa0\x80
@manirostom we couldn\xe2\x80\x99t agree more.\xc2\xa0
\xe2\xa0\x80
That\xe2\x80\x99s why we launched the Victory Swim Collection.\xc2\xa0A range of swimwear for modest women, so no matter their beliefs or values, not a single one of them has to leave the water anymore.
\xc2\xa0\xe2\xa0\x80
#YouCantStopUs #VictorySwim
\xc2\xa0\xe2\xa0\x80
:movie_camera:: @saradunlop and @dominicleungcuts'

b'@kingjames\xc2\xa0has been the people\xe2\x80\x99s champ ever since he stole the spotlight as a teen. But he\xe2\x80\x99s also a champion of the people, using his platform to ensure all the voices in his community are heard and counted.\xc2\xa0:crown:
\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\x80\x9cIt\xe2\x80\x99s about all of us looking in the mirror and saying what can we do better to help change?\xe2\x80\x9c LeBron knows that change doesn\xe2\x80\x99t happen overnight, so his fight for representation goes way beyond the November US election. He\xe2\x80\x99s got big plans, but if anyone can pull them off, it\xe2\x80\x99s King James.\xc2\xa0
\xe2\xa0\x80
Visit the link in our bio for information on voting\xc2\xa0:ballot_box_with_ballot_selector:'
b"You don't need to be a star to have a voice. #YouCantStopOurVoice\n\xe2\xa0\x80\nClick the link in bio to learn more."

b'@marcusrashford has earned a nod from the Queen and raised \xc2\xa320 million. The forward for England\xe2\x80\x99s National team is continuing his campaign to end child food poverty in the UK. :clapping_hands:
\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\x80\x9cI think if we do it right we can change what the future looks like.\xe2\x80\x9d By rallying both the government and the food industry together, Marcus is using his platform to ensure that all school kids have access to meals. Give him a follow to watch how he makes history, both on the pitch and in schools.
\xe2\xa0\x80
In this series, we\xe2\x80\x99re highlighting exceptional athletes like Marcus who fight the good fight for what they believe in.
\xe2\xa0\x80
:movie_camera:: @joshblaaberg and @joelhoneywell'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cThe girls I coach look up to me. I always tell them, \xe2\x80\x98Do your homework, get good grades. And remember, always stay in sports.\xe2\x80\x99\xe2\x80\x9d
\xe2\xa0\x80
From coaching the local girls team in North London to refereeing FA football matches, this is the energy @jawahir_roble (lovingly known as JJ) always brings to the pitch.
\xe2\xa0\x80
JJ is the UK\xe2\x80\x99s first hijab-wearing, female referee. In our new series, we\xe2\x80\x99ll spotlight inspiring change-makers like her and all of the significant work they do for their communities.
\xe2\xa0\x80
Click the link in our bio to learn more about her story. :camera_with_flash: @ronanksm'

b'When they say there\xe2\x80\x99s no way,\xc2\xa0show them one.\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0
\xe2\xa0\x80
Faced with an unimaginable choice between giving up what she was born to do, or changing who she was born to be, @castersemenya800m, has instead chosen to continue her fight to be herself in the sport she loves.\xc2\xa0:raising_hands:
\xe2\xa0\x80
#YouCantStopUs'
b"When one of us wins, we both win.\xc2\xa0You can't stop sisters.\xc2\xa0#YouCantStopUs\n\xc2\xa0\nJoin us. Link in bio."

b'We will continue to stand up for equality and work to break down barriers for athletes* all over the world. We will do and invest more to uphold\xc2\xa0longstanding commitment in supporting the Black community and partnering with world-class organizations dedicated to ensuring racial equality, social justice, and greater access to education. \xe2\xa0\x80\n\xe2\xa0\x80\nFor more information, please click the link in the bio.'
b'Let\xe2\x80\x99s all be part of the change. \xe2\xa0\x80\n\xe2\xa0\x80\n#UntilWeAllWin'

b"Today, we're not playing for a trophy. We're playing for something much bigger. #PlayForTheWorld"

b'\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\x80\x9cI think it is really important for black women to see themselves in others. We need to start sharing our stories more. We need to find ways to support each other, talk about hair and running because my gosh it\xe2\x80\x99s hard. And also celebrate each other.\xe2\x80\x9d - @j_nesi
\xe2\xa0\x80
The final episode of the Common Thread series with Uninterrupted highlights those who relentlessly go forward together, from the track to the streets. Celebrating the power of sport to create community, inclusivity and sisterhood, athletes @vashtizzle, Jasmine Nesi of @rungrlco, and @sahraisha of\xc2\xa0@asra.club emphasize how our strides are united, moving through a marathon of collective progress.\xc2\xa0#BHM #UntilWeAllWin
\xe2\xa0\x80
:speaking_head_selector::\xc2\xa0Vashti Cunningham
:movie_camera::\xc2\xa0@childotu'

b'They wanted you to smile more.
They wanted you to be more polite.
They wanted you to scream a little softer.
They wanted you to be less aggressive when you won.
They wanted you to walk away when you made mistakes.
But instead of just becoming the player the game wanted?
You became the player it needed.'
b'\xe2\xa0\x80\n\xe2\xa0\x80\n(sound on)'

b'\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\x80\x9cMy color doesn\xe2\x80\x99t stop me from doing what I want to do. We\xe2\x80\x99re all playing with the same ball, we\xe2\x80\x99re playing with eleven players on each side. Football isn\xe2\x80\x99t made for a certain person. Football is a universal language, anyone can play it.\xe2\x80\x9d - Debra Nelson
\xe2\xa0\x80
The second episode of the Common Thread series featuring Debra Nelson (@FootballBeyondBorders), @its_kairabaaa (@fcharlem) and @cdunn19 (@uswnt) focuses on sport\xe2\x80\x99s ability to transcend borders and boundaries with something as simple as a ball and a goal.
\xe2\xa0\x80
:speaking_head_selector:: Crystal Dunn
:movie_camera:: @childotu'

b'\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\x80\x9cRepresentation matters, and you can\xe2\x80\x99t become something that you don\xe2\x80\x99t see.\xe2\x80\x9d - @Ingridsilva
\xe2\xa0\x80
Together, a prodigy from Brazil who became the face of modern ballet, and a young dancer in Florida uplifting anyone who sees him move are united by a common thread.
\xe2\xa0\x80
The first episode of the Common Thread series focuses on representation in sport, with athletes Ingrid Silva and @alexanderrthomass\xc2\xa0showing the next generation what is possible when we believe our passions cannot be limited, and no barriers can hold us back. #UntilWeAllWin
\xe2\xa0\x80
:speaking_head_selector::\xc2\xa0@serenawilliams
:movie_camera::\xc2\xa0@childotu'

b'\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\x80\x9cIt doesn\xe2\x80\x99t matter if you\xe2\x80\x99re in a wheelchair, in your 80s, or what race or gender you are. Everybody can play tennis.\xe2\x80\x9d - @dylanalcott
\xe2\xa0\x80
Dylan is more than a top tennis player. He has used his success on the court as a vehicle to challenge perceptions about disabled people and push for inclusivity universally. \xe2\x80\x9cIf you have a body, you really are an athlete,\xe2\x80\x9d says Dylan.
\xe2\xa0\x80
This is how you change the game. #justdoit'
b'The Future of Sport is here. #Nike2020\n\xe2\xa0\x80\nHead to our link in bio to join us.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cAt first, my abuela, she didn\xe2\x80\x99t get it. \xe2\x80\x98Dalia, it\xe2\x80\x99s too rough for a girl. Your mom was a cheerleader \xe2\x80\x93 why don\xe2\x80\x99t you be a cheerleader?\xe2\x80\x99 Football is where I get my strength. Where I prove that nothing is off-limits. Where I can be whatever I want.\xe2\x80\x9d
\xe2\xa0\x80
Dalia Hurtado\xe2\x80\x99s family had specific expectations of her: Work hard, get good grades, and follow in her mother\xe2\x80\x99s footsteps as a cheerleader. But cheering on the sideline was never an option for Dalia.
\xe2\xa0\x80
As a kid in Mexico, she was the only girl who would play soccer with the boys, and after moving back to East LA with her abuela, she set her sights on football. At 16, she became the only girl to make the varsity team at her high school. Two years later, she\xe2\x80\x99s inspired more girls to play football at her high school.
\xe2\xa0\x80
Through football, Dalia is re-writing the story her family wrote for her, breaking through stereotypes, and empowering her community to do the same \xe2\x80\x93 one game at a time.'
b"Mamba forever.\nOur condolences to Kobe and Gianna's family and everyone involved in today\xe2\x80\x99s tragedy."

b'\xe2\x80\x9cEveryone deserves the right to be well. It\xe2\x80\x99s just a matter of investing in it.\xe2\x80\x9d\xc2\xa0@nicoleacardoza is invested in helping close the wellness gap.
\xe2\xa0\x80
Thanks to a donation based yoga class in college, Nicole was able to feel at home in her body for the first time. Ever since, she\xe2\x80\x99s made it her mission to help others experience the same.
\xe2\xa0\x80
Whether introducing kids to mindfulness in school through @yogaFoster, or investing in underestimated entrepreneurs through @ReclamationVentures, she\xe2\x80\x99s helping change the landscape of wellness for good.
\xe2\xa0\x80
Because Yoga should not have a type. Yoga is for all.'
